Nulliparous to Pregnancy Trimester:

Calculate a new variable with Null as 0, and trimester as 1,2,3 and Select variables of interest, remove 21116 and 20827, create the matrix

preg.tri.null <-repro.extra %>% 
  mutate(null.tri = if_else(is.na(repro.extra$was.preg) | repro.extra$was.preg == FALSE, 
                            "0", 
                            repro.extra$trimester)) %>% 
  filter(reprostat == "pregnant" | reprostat == "nulliparous") %>% 
  filter(uncchdid != "21116", uncchdid !="20827") %>%
  select(uncchdid, reprostat, MDS1, MDS2, SES3, null.tri) %>% 
  na.omit()

preg.tri.null$null.tri <-as.factor(preg.tri.null$null.tri)

Create the matrix for pregnancy

Pregnancy Trimester: CORRECTED EWAS

preg.tri.null$null.tri <-as.factor(preg.tri.null$null.tri)

preg.tri.null$null.tri <-relevel(preg.tri.null$null.tri, ref = "0")

# Setup the design matrix. ---- 
design <- model.matrix(~0 + null.tri +  MDS1 + MDS2 + SES3, data = preg.tri.null);



colnames(design)[1:4]<- c("nulliparous", "first.trimester","second.trimester", "third.trimester")


contrast.matrix<- makeContrasts(N2F = "first.trimester-nulliparous", N2S = "second.trimester-nulliparous", N2T = "third.trimester-nulliparous", levels=design);


# Run the EWAS and smooth the variance ---- 
preg.tri.null.ewas <-lmFit(matrix.corrected, design, na.action = na.omit)
preg.tri.null.ewas <- contrasts.fit(preg.tri.null.ewas, contrast.matrix) 
preg.tri.null.ewas <- eBayes(preg.tri.null.ewas)
preg.tri.null.ewas.var5 <-preg.tri.null.ewas[c(mvals.var5[,1]), ]

# Pull only probes with >5% variability ---- 
preg.tri.null.ewas.var5.results <-decideTests(preg.tri.null.ewas.var5, adjust.method = "BH", p.value = 0.05)

# Summary data ---- 
summary(preg.tri.null.ewas.var5.results) %>%
  kable("html") %>%
  kable_styling()
N2F N2S N2T
Down 0 300 342
NotSig 110631 110321 110264
Up 0 10 25 
# Ok, for all of them there are SOME significantly different probes...

vennDiagram(preg.tri.null.ewas.var5.results[,c(2,3)], include = c("up", "down"),counts.col = c("red", "blue"))

Pregnancy Trimester: CORRECTED EWAS

preg.tri$trimester <-as.factor(preg.tri$trimester)

preg.tri$trimester <-relevel(preg.tri$trimester, ref = "first.trimester")

# Setup the design matrix. ---- 
design <- model.matrix(~0 + trimester + pregord + twins + MDS1 + MDS2 + SES3, data = preg.tri);



colnames(design)[1:3]<- c("first.trimester","second.trimester", "third.trimester")


contrast.matrix<- makeContrasts(F2S = "second.trimester-first.trimester", F2T = "third.trimester-first.trimester", S2T = "third.trimester-second.trimester", levels=design);


# Run the EWAS and smooth the variance ---- 
preg.tri.ewas <-lmFit(matrix.corrected, design, na.action = na.omit)
preg.tri.ewas <- contrasts.fit(preg.tri.ewas, contrast.matrix) 
preg.tri.ewas <- eBayes(preg.tri.ewas)
preg.tri.ewas.var5 <-preg.tri.ewas[c(mvals.var5[,1]), ]

# Pull only probes with >5% variability ---- 
preg.tri.ewas.var5.results <-decideTests(preg.tri.ewas.var5, adjust.method = "BH", p.value = 0.05)

# Summary data ---- 
summary(preg.tri.ewas.var5.results) %>%
  kable("html") %>%
  kable_styling()
F2S F2T S2T
Down 0 15 0
NotSig 110631 110616 110631
Up 0 0 0 
# Ok, for all of them there are SOME significantly different probes...

vennDiagram(preg.tri.ewas.var5.results, include = c("up", "down"),counts.col = c("red", "blue"))

# Setup the design matrix. ---- 
design <- model.matrix(~0 + null.bf  +  MDS1 + MDS2 + SES3, data = lact.null);



colnames(design)[1:4]<- c("nulliparous", "zero_6mo","sixmo_12mo", "over_1yr")


contrast.matrix<- makeContrasts(N2F = "zero_6mo-nulliparous", 
                                N2S = "sixmo_12mo-nulliparous", 
                                N2T = "over_1yr-nulliparous", levels=design);


# Run the EWAS and smooth the variance ---- 
lact.null.ewas <-lmFit(matrix.corrected, design, na.action = na.omit)
lact.null.ewas <- contrasts.fit(lact.null.ewas, contrast.matrix)
